xboing (1.0.6-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Editor play-test now matches the original: it no longer depletes lives,
    never triggers game-over or the bonus screen on a cleared test board, and
    returns to the editor with your in-progress board, level name, and cursor
    intact. The p and Escape keys end the test cleanly (no window flash or drop
    to the attract screens); Q is ignored during play-test as in the original.
  * Fix ball death to match the original: a 3-life game now gives four balls
    (game-over fires one death later, as in 1996), and the paddle grows back to
    maximum size after every ball loss — a forgiveness mechanic that had been
    missing.
  * Fix the attract-screen score animation leaking a fake score into the editor
    HUD; the editor now shows a zeroed score on entry.

 -- J Freeman <jmf@pobox.com>  Sun, 12 Jul 2026 19:19:01 -0700

xboing (1.0.5-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix the ammo belt desyncing from the end-of-level bullet bonus under
    unlimited ammo. The MAXAMMO block hid the belt (showing no bullets) while
    firing still worked and the bonus rewarded the full count; the belt now
    draws the real count, matching the original and the bonus.
  * Guard against a crafted save file inflating the ammo count: gun ammo is
    now clamped to a legitimate maximum, so a tampered save can no longer make
    the HUD issue thousands of draws per frame or award an inflated bonus.
  * Fix the level editor writing "Untitled" over a level's real name on save.
    Loading a level, editing, and saving now preserves the name, and renaming
    in the editor updates the on-screen title immediately.

 -- J Freeman <jmf@pobox.com>  Sun, 12 Jul 2026 10:51:18 -0700

xboing (1.0.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Full level-editor parity with the 1996 original. The SDL2 editor had
    never been through a parity audit and was silently corrupting levels on
    re-save; this release fixes the data-integrity bugs and rebuilds the UI
    to match the original.
  * Fix the editor writing a hardcoded 120-second time bonus over every
    level's real value (only 6 of 80 levels are 120, so re-saving corrupted
    92.5% of them), and fix counter-block hit-counts and RANDOM blocks being
    lost on save.
  * Real modal save/load/set-time/set-name/clear/quit dialogues with an
    unsaved-work safety net, replacing stubs that silently auto-confirmed.
  * Faithful editor UI: two-column tool palette with all 30 entries and the
    Active indicator, in-editor HUD, red grid drawn under the blocks, and 2px
    red borders around the palette panel. Right-click inspects a block's
    point value; Shift+left-click erases (reachable without the physical
    middle mouse button the 1996 Sun/X11 hardware assumed). (ADR-057..ADR-062.)

 -- J Freeman <jmf@pobox.com>  Sun, 12 Jul 2026 08:24:17 -0700

xboing (1.0.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix the attract-cycle high-score screen showing a blank Hall of Fame on
    installs with no shared/global board (Homebrew, dev builds). It now falls
    back to the player's personal board when the global board is empty.
    (ADR-054.)
  * Fix the game-over flag leaking into the attract screens. After a game
    over, the first Space on the high-score screen now starts a game instead
    of advancing the attract loop; the flag is cleared on returning to the
    title. (ADR-055.)
  * Fix a failed level load dropping straight into an empty bonus screen. The
    game now refuses to start and returns to the title when a level file
    cannot be loaded, instead of entering gameplay with an empty grid.
    (ADR-056.)

 -- J Freeman <jmf@pobox.com>  Sat, 11 Jul 2026 12:24:04 -0700

xboing (1.0.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Faithful X11 editor cursors: the level editor now shows the real X11
    plus (XC_plus) while drawing and skull-and-crossbones (XC_pirate) while
    erasing, rebuilt from the original cursor-font bitmaps. (ADR-051.)
  * Fix cursor state leaking between screens. Every screen now sets its own
    cursor explicitly: the plain arrow on all menu/attract screens, hidden
    during gameplay, plus/skull in the editor. Entering the instructions
    screen after the editor no longer shows the leftover crosshair.
    (ADR-052.)
  * Space on the title screen now opens the instructions screen (the next
    attract screen) instead of starting the game, and a single keypress on
    boot can no longer cascade several screens straight into the game.
    Attract-screen Space is handled once per visual frame, matching the C
    cycle key. (ADR-053.)
  * Wire the -grab command-line flag to confine the mouse pointer to the
    game window (SDL_SetWindowMouseGrab), restoring the original's behaviour.

 -- J Freeman <jmf@pobox.com>  Fri, 03 Jul 2026 17:31:57 -0700

xboing (1.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix the between-level bonus interstitial reporting the wrong high-score
    rank (e.g. "1st" when the player finished 2nd). It now predicts
    placement against the board the player competes on (personal when no
    global board exists) using the same slot logic as the actual insert.
    Also stop prompting for boing-master "words of wisdom" on installs with
    no global board, where the text was silently discarded. (ADR-050.)

